<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
   <meta charset="UTF-8">
   <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
   <title>User Survey Report</title>
</head>
<body>

  <style>
    body {
      font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      height: 100vh;
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
    }

    .login-container {
      background-color: #fff;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    .login-form {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    h2 {
      text-align: center;
      color: #1b2f45;
    }

    .input-group {
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    label {
      color: #1b2f45;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    input[type="text"],
    input[type="password"] {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 8px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      outline: none;
    }

    button {
      background-color: #1b2f45;
      color: #fff;
      border: none;
      padding: 10px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    button:hover {
      background-color: #0e1a29;
    }

    .back-to-home {
        position: absolute;
        top: 10px;
        left: 10px;
        background-color: #1b2f45;
        color: #fff;
        border: none;
        padding: 10px 15px;
        border-radius: 5px;
        text-decoration: none;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .back-to-home:hover {
        background-color: #0e1a29;
    }
    
  </style>

      <!-- Add a form with a dropdown for filtering by user ID -->
      <form action="/report" method="post">
        <label for="userIdFilter">Filter by User ID:</label>
        <select name="userIdFilter" id="userIdFilter">
          <!-- Add an "All" option -->
          <option value="all" selected>All</option>
          <!-- Populate the dropdown options with sorted distinct user IDs -->
          <% for (let i = 0; i < sortedUserIds.length; i++) { %>
            <option value="<%= sortedUserIds[i] %>"><%= sortedUserIds[i] %></option>
          <% } %>
        </select>
        <button type="submit">Filter</button>
      </form>

   <label><b>User Information:</b></label>
   <br><br>
   <table style="width: 100%; background-color: antiquewhite; border: 1px solid black;">
     <thead style="background-color: cornflowerblue; color: white;">
       <tr>
         <th style="text-align: left;">User ID</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">Timestamp</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">City</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">1. What is your age?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">2. Gender</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">3. Relationship Status</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">4. Occupation Status</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">5. What type of organizations are you affiliated with?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">6. Do you use social media?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">7. What social media platforms do you commonly use?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">8. What is the average time you spend on social media every day?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">9. How often do you find yourself using Social media without a specific purpose?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">10. How often do you get distracted by Social media when you are busy doing something?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">11. Do you feel restless if you haven't used Social media in a while?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">12. On a scale of 1 to 5, how easily distracted are you?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">13. On a scale of 1 to 5, how much are you bothered by worries?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">14. Do you find it difficult to concentrate on things?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">15. On a scale of 1-5, how often do you compare yourself to other successful people through the use of social media?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">16. Following the previous question, how do you feel about these comparisons, generally speaking?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">17. How often do you look to seek validation from features of social media?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">18. How often do you feel depressed or down?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">19. On a scale of 1 to 5, how frequently does your interest in daily activities fluctuate?</th>
         <th style="text-align: left;">20. On a scale of 1 to 5, how often do you face issues regarding sleep?</th>
         <th></th>
         <th></th>
       </tr>
     </thead>
     <tbody style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
      <% for (let iCount = 0; iCount < myuser.length; iCount++) { %>
         <tr>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].user_id %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].timestamp %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].city %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].age %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].gender %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].relationship_status %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].occupation_status %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].organization_affiliation %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].social_media_use %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].social_media_platform %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].time_usage %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].use_without_purpose %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].distracted_by_social_media %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].restless_without_social_media %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].easily_distracted %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].bothered_by_worries %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].concentration_difficulty %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].compare_self_to_others %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].opinions_about_comparisons %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].seek_validation %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].feel_depressed %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].daily_activity_interest_fluctuations %></td>
           <td><%= myuser[iCount].sleep_issues %></td>
         </tr>
      <% } %>
     </tbody>
   </table>
   <a href="/" class="back-to-home">Go back to Home</a>
</body>
</html>